From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v51 - trace setup_dig_transmitter/encoder args + PIXCLK_RESYNC dump

After v50 (patch 0024) traced every ATOM master/sub-table call, three
candidate hypotheses remained for why the bridge cq_wait_set still hangs
3 seconds despite all ATOM calls returning ret=0:

  H1: UNIPHYTransmitterControl (idx 0x4c) is being called with wrong args
      — wrong UNIPHY block (e.g., UNIPHYA when PS4 wiring needs UNIPHYE),
      wrong link rate, wrong lane count.
  H2: PIXCLK_RESYNC_CNTL routing isn't picking up our v49 ATOM_PPLL2 —
      v45 dumps showed PIXCLK1_RESYNC_CNTL=0x1 (others=0); we need to
      verify ATOM SetPixelClock v6 updated this routing.
  H3: Skip-DP-link-train (patch 0006) starves the bridge of TPS pattern
      that the MN864729 actually needs to lock.

H1 and H2 are visibility-only. H3 is a behavior change. Bundle H1 + H2
in one patch (visibility stacks safely); save H3 for v52 if H1+H2
don't yield a clear answer.

Three instrumentation points, all gated on CHIP_LIVERPOOL/CHIP_GLADIUS:

  1. atombios_encoders.c::amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_encoder
     (just before the ATOM execute_table call at line 739):
     - print action (ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_*: 0x0f SETUP, 0x0d DP_VIDEO_ON,
       0x0c DP_VIDEO_OFF, 0x08-0x0b LINK_TRAINING phases)
     - frev/crev (which version of args was used)
     - encoder_id, dig_encoder, pixel_clock, dp_clock, dp_lane_count,
       hpd_id

  2. atombios_encoders.c::amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_transmitter
     (just before the ATOM execute_table call at line 1143):
     - print action (ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_*:
         0 DISABLE        1 ENABLE
         7 INIT           8 DISABLE_OUTPUT
         9 ENABLE_OUTPUT  10 SETUP
         11 SETUP_VSEMPH  12 POWER_ON   13 POWER_OFF)
     - frev/crev, encoder_id (which UNIPHY block A/B/C/D/E/F)
     - dig_encoder, pll_id, is_dp, dp_clock, dp_lane_count
     - lane_num, lane_set (function params), connector_object_id, hpd_id

  3. dce_v8_0.c::dce_v8_0_crtc_mode_set (immediately after
     amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_pll):
     - read mmPIXCLK0_RESYNC_CNTL, mmPIXCLK1_RESYNC_CNTL,
       mmPIXCLK2_RESYNC_CNTL
     - print the trio along with crtc_id and pll_id

The v50 trace showed UNIPHYTransmitterControl runs 3 times during
modeset and DIGxEncoderControl 3 times. With H1 visibility we'll see
which actions and which UNIPHY block. With H2 we'll see whether ATOM
updated the PIXCLK routing for our PPLL2 selection.

Expected v51 output excerpt during the second-cycle modeset:

  ps4_atom: AdjustDisplayPll v1.3 OUT r=0 freq=270000 ...
  ps4_atom: SetPixelClock IN ... pll=1 ref=2 fb=118 ...
  ps4_atom: SetPixelClock OUT r=0
  ps4_atom: post-SetPixelClock PIXCLK0/1/2 RESYNC: 0xN 0xN 0xN crtc_id=0 pll_id=1
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0f (SETUP) frev=1 crev=4 enc_id=0xNNNN dig=N ...
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=7 (INIT) ...
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=10 (SETUP) ...
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=1 (ENABLE) enc_id=0xNNNN ...
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0d (DP_VIDEO_ON) ...

What it answers:

  - encoder_id printed in tx + enc traces tells us which UNIPHY block.
    Standard CIK encoder_ids (atombios_encoders.h):
      0x1F INTERNAL_KLDSCP_LVTMA
      0x1E INTERNAL_UNIPHY    (== UNIPHY1 / "UNIPHYA")
      0x1F INTERNAL_KLDSCP_LVTMA
      0x20 INTERNAL_UNIPHY1   (UNIPHYC/D)
      0x21 INTERNAL_UNIPHY2   (UNIPHYE/F)
    v48/v49 trace showed enc_id=30 (0x1E = INTERNAL_UNIPHY) — first UNIPHY.
    If PS4 wiring routes the bridge to UNIPHYE/F, this is wrong and we
    need to override.

  - PIXCLK_RESYNC values tell us which PPLL drives which PIXCLK output.
    If PIXCLK1=0x1 means "PIXCLK1 is enabled, sourced from PPLL?" we'll
    learn whether PPLL2 (our pick) is the actual source.

If H1 reveals wrong UNIPHY selection, v52 forces it. If H2 reveals wrong
PPLL routing, v52 fixes the routing. If both look correct, v52 disables
patch 0006 to test H3.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_encoders.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_encoders.c
@@ -736,6 +736,14 @@
 		break;
 	}

+	/* v51 H1a: trace setup_dig_encoder args on Liverpool/Gladius. action
+	 * decoded from atombios.h ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_*: 0x0f=SETUP, 0x0d=DP_VIDEO_ON,
+	 * 0x0c=DP_VIDEO_OFF, 0x08-0x0b=DP_LINK_TRAINING phases. */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+		pr_info("ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x%02x frev=%u crev=%u enc_id=0x%04x dig=%d pclk=%u dp_clk=%d dp_lanes=%d hpd=%d\n",
+			action, frev, crev, amdgpu_encoder->encoder_id,
+			dig->dig_encoder, amdgpu_encoder->pixel_clock,
+			dp_clock, dp_lane_count, hpd_id);
 	amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));

 }
@@ -1140,6 +1148,19 @@
 		break;
 	}

+	/* v51 H1b: trace setup_dig_transmitter args on Liverpool/Gladius. action
+	 * decoded from atombios.h ATOM_TRANSMITTER_ACTION_*:
+	 *   0=DISABLE 1=ENABLE 7=INIT 8=DISABLE_OUTPUT 9=ENABLE_OUTPUT
+	 *  10=SETUP  11=SETUP_VSEMPH  12=POWER_ON  13=POWER_OFF
+	 * Most important fields for diagnosis: action (which phase),
+	 * encoder_id (which UNIPHY block — A/B/C/D/E/F), pll_id (which PPLL
+	 * the TX uses as ref clock), dp_clock/dp_lane_count (link config),
+	 * dig_encoder (which DIG block 0/1), connector_object_id (HDMI A/B). */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+		pr_info("ps4_atom: dig_tx action=%d frev=%u crev=%u enc_id=0x%04x dig=%d pll=%d is_dp=%d dp_clk=%d dp_lanes=%d lane_num=%u lane_set=0x%02x conn_obj=0x%04x hpd=%d\n",
+			action, frev, crev, amdgpu_encoder->encoder_id,
+			dig_encoder, pll_id, is_dp, dp_clock, dp_lane_count,
+			lane_num, lane_set, connector_object_id, hpd_id);
 	amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));
 }

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/dce_v8_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/dce_v8_0.c
@@ -2562,6 +2562,7 @@
 				  int x, int y, struct drm_framebuffer *old_fb)
 {
 	struct amdgpu_crtc *amdgpu_crtc = to_amdgpu_crtc(crtc);
+	struct amdgpu_device *adev = drm_to_adev(crtc->dev);

 	if (!amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock) {
 		/* v28: PS4 ATOM BIOS sometimes returns 0 from
@@ -2579,6 +2580,18 @@
 	}

 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_pll(crtc, adjusted_mode);
+	/* v51 H2: dump PIXCLKn_RESYNC_CNTL on Liverpool/Gladius right after
+	 * SetPixelClock to verify PPLL→CRTC routing. v45 dumps showed
+	 * PIXCLK1_RESYNC_CNTL=0x1 (others=0) — likely PIXCLK1 selects
+	 * which PPLL drives our active CRTC, but we don't know if our
+	 * v49 pll_id=ATOM_PPLL2 is actually routed there. ATOM SetPixelClock
+	 * v6 should have programmed the routing; this dump confirms. */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+		pr_info("ps4_atom: post-SetPixelClock PIXCLK0/1/2 RESYNC: 0x%08x 0x%08x 0x%08x  crtc_id=%d pll_id=%d\n",
+			RREG32(mmPIXCLK0_RESYNC_CNTL),
+			RREG32(mmPIXCLK1_RESYNC_CNTL),
+			RREG32(mmPIXCLK2_RESYNC_CNTL),
+			amdgpu_crtc->crtc_id, amdgpu_crtc->pll_id);
 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_dtd_timing(crtc, adjusted_mode);
 	dce_v8_0_crtc_do_set_base(crtc, old_fb, x, y, 0);
 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_overscan_setup(crtc, mode, adjusted_mode);
